content.description: Start with hands in slanting crack.  Set foot on good ledge and dead-point to lip.  Very core intensive and very hard.
content.location: Upper left section of talus just around the left from Fantasticorner.

content.description: Start from a stand, right hand in the arete and left probably on an inverted pinch below the lip.  Climb up the arete, mantle and finish with easing but airy climbing.  A fall off to the right could be really bad so pad and spot, and of course climb accordingly.
content.protection: More pads the better and spotters.
content.location: Just above the north corner of the last parking lot of the north shore.  The block is obvious and prominent.

content.description: Start standing with a good juglet in a seam for the left hand, and a juggy sidepull for the right.  Climb the left side of the arete, moving slightly left to mantle.
content.location: Just below the prominent Uncut Gems Boulder.  Just above the north side of the last parking lot on the North Shore.  The problem faces uphill.

content.description: Start low with large meat-hook and climb up block on right side of boulder.
content.location: Larger boulder up hill and left up Fantasticorner, near the northern end of talus.

content.description: SDS with long rail on right side of boulder.  Work your way up left to great ledges.
content.location: Tucked away up in the upper left section of talus, Just right of The Winter Blues.

content.description: Start on the obvious two edges back in the cave. Place a solid toe jam and work the moves along the sloping edges and pinch out of the tight cave maintaining tension and body positions to prevent dabbing. Following the toe jam release crux, set up into the start holds of Gnarls Barkley and finish it off.
content.protection: 2+ pads and a puffy jacket (for the jutting rocks at the mouth of the cave)
content.location: Directly below High Radiance/Low Radiance boulder. Can be seen from the starting position of High Radiance by looking beneath the boulder.

content.description: Start standing high, with a good left hand pinch, and an inverted undercling pinch for the right just on the edge of the roof.  Pull on, perhaps get a toe hook and shuffle up some holds.  Better holds are gained and an airy but not so hard finish awaits.
content.location: Just right of Gnarls Barkley, just left of Uncut Gems and sharing the same finish.  On a big, prominent boulder 100 feet above the northeast corner of the last parking lot on the North Shore. The climb faces northwest.

content.description: A cluster of boulder problems at the north end of the boulder field.
